office of accessible education types of accommodations student affairs office of accessible education students faculty & teaching staff about the oae schwab learning center resources & faqs stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit types of accommodations accommodation process types of accommodations exam accommodations for students with disabilities types of accommodations office of accessible education faculty & teaching staff the oae provides many different kinds of disability related accommodations services and auxiliary aids depending on the student's particular needs when determining academic adjustments the basic principle of an individualized case by case analysis underlies all accommodations decisions that is there is no rule about what accommodations are always appropriate for every circumstance or that all faculty should always provide certain accommodations for all students with a particular disability accommodation decisions take into consideration the tasks involved the particular setting and institutional standards and guidelines some common types of accommodations include alternate format materials note takers accommodated examinations eg extended time use of a scribe sign language interpreters captioned films reduced course load library or laboratory assistant audio describer for students with visual impairments accommodation process up exam accommodations for students with disabilities groups office of accessible education printer friendly version calendar search oae search oae information location & hours disgo cart service jobs at the oae office of accessible education 563 salvatierra walk stanford california 94305 650 723 1066 voice 650 725 5301 fax im oaegetinfo provide feedback copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
